on football forwards]]\n[[Category:FK Partizani Tirana players]]\n[[Category:Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K. footballers]]\n[[Category:NK Zagreb players]]\n[[Category:Reggina 1914 players]]\n[[Category:U.S. Salernitana 1919 players]]\n[[Category:Hellas Verona F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Robur Siena players]]\n[[Category:A.C. ChievoVerona players]]\n[[Category:A.S. Livorno Calcio players]]\n[[Category:A.C. Cesena players]]\n[[Category:Albanian Superliga players]]\n[[Category:S\u00fcper Lig players]]\n[[Category:Serie A players]]\n[[Category:Serie B players]]\n[[Category:Croatian First Football League players]]\n[[Category:Albania youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Albania under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Albania international footballers]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 1997 Mediterranean Games]]\n[[Category:Albanian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Albanian expatriate sportspeople in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Albanian expatriate sportspeople in Croatia]]\n[[Category:Albanian expatriate sportspeople in Italy]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Croatia]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Italy]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2014}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Erjon Bogdani\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Erjon Bogdani\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1977|4|14}}\n| birth_place    = [[Tirana]], Albania\n| height         = 1.91 m\n| position       = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub    = [[Albania national under-19 football team|Albania U19]] (manager)\n| youthyears1 = 1987\u20131994 | youthclubs1 = [[KF Partizani Tirana|Partizani Tirana]]\n| years1  = 1994\u20131997 | clubs1  = [[KF Partizani Tirana|Partizani Tirana]] | caps1  = 62 | goals1  = 21\n| years2  = 1997\u20131998 | clubs2  = [[Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K.|Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi]]   | caps2  = 11 | goals2  = 1\n| years3  = 1998\u20132000 | clubs3  = [[NK Zagreb|Zagreb]]                     | caps3  = 25 | goals3  = 8\n| years4  = 2000\u20132004 | clubs4  = [[Reggina Calcio|Reggina]]               | caps4  = 67 | goals4  = 11\n| years5  = 2003\u20132004 | clubs5  = \u2192 [[Salernitana Calcio 1919|Salernitana]] (loan) | caps5 = 38 | goals5  = 8\n| years6  = 2004\u20132005 | clubs6  = [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Verona]]            | caps6  = 38 | goals6  = 17\n| years7  = 2005\u20132007 | clubs7  = [[A.C. Siena|Siena]]                     | caps7  = 49 | goals7  = 13\n| years8  = 2007\u20132010 | clubs8  = [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]]             | caps8  = 61 | goals8  = 8\n| years9  = 2007\u20132008 | clubs9  = \u2192 [[A.S. Livorno Calcio|Livorno]] (loan) | caps9  = 17 | goals9  = 2\n| years10 = 2010\u20132012 | clubs10 = [[A.C. Cesena|Cesena]]                   | caps10 = 49 | goals10 = 8\n| years11 = 2012\u20132013 | clubs11 = [[A.C. Siena|Siena]]                     | caps11 = 29 | goals11 = 6\n| totalcaps = 466 | totalgoals = 103\n| nationalyears1 = 1996\u20131998 | nationalteam1 = [[Albania national under-21 football team|Albania U21]] | nationalcaps1 = 8  | nationalgoals1 = 2\n| nationalyears2 = 1997      | nationalteam2 = [[Albania national under-23 football team|Albania U23]] | nationalcaps2 = 1  | nationalgoals2 = 1\n| nationalyears3 = 1996\u20132013 | nationalteam3 = [[Albania national football team|Albania]]              | nationalcaps3 = 74 | nationalgoals3 = 18\n| medaltemplates = \n| manageryears1 = 2015 | managerclubs1 = [[Albania national football team|Albania]] (Assistant)\n| manageryears2 = 2016\u2013     | managerclubs2 = [[Albania national under-19 football team|Albania U19]]\n}}\n\n'''Erjon Bogdani''' (born 14 April 1977) is an Albanian professional [[Association football|football]] coach and former player who is the current [[Manager (association football)|manager]] of [[Albania national under-19 football team|Albania under-19 team]]. He is nicknamed \"Bogu\" or \"Er-Bomber\".<ref>[http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/receta-e-bogdanit-ja-si-mund-ta-mundim-danimarken/ \u201cReceta\u201d e Bogdanit: Ja si mund ta mundim Danimark\u00ebn] ''[[Panorama Sport]]''</ref><ref name=\"Er-Bomber\"/>\n\nRegarded as one of the most successful Albanian players of all time,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/partizani-fton-bogdanin-eshte-nder-te-vish-te-ne-lika-lojtareve-po-u-mesojme-derbin/|title=Partizani fton Bogdanin: \u00cbsht\u00eb nder t\u00eb vish te ne. Lika: Lojtar\u00ebve po u m\u00ebsojm\u00eb derbin|trans-title=Partizani invites Bogdani: It's an honour to come to us. Lika: We are teaching the derby to players|publisher=Panorama Sport|language=Albanian|date=5 October 2013|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref> Bogdani began his career at [[KF Partizani Tirana|Partizani Tirana]] in 1994 where he debuted at the age of 16. He left the club in January 1998 to sign with [[Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K.|Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi]].<ref name=\"Career\">{{cite web|url=http://www.oranews.tv/article/erjon-bogdani-mund-te-lere-futbollin|title=Erjon Bogdani mund t\u00eb l\u00ebr\u00eb futbollin|trans-title=Erjon Bogdani can leave football|publisher=Ora News|language=Albanian|date=4 October 2013|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref> That summer, Bogdani moved in Croatia to play for [[NK Zagreb|Zagreb]],<ref name=\"Career\"/> before traveling to Italy where he enjoyed the best years of his career.<ref name=\"Career\"/>\n\nBogdani played in the following years in [[Serie A]] and [[Serie B|B]], representing [[Urbs Reggina 1914|Reggina]], [[Salernitana Calcio 1919|Salernitana]], [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Verona]], [[A.C. Siena|Siena]], [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]], [[A.S. Livorno Calcio|Livorno]] and [[A.C. Cesena|Cesena]].<ref name=\"Career\"/> He became a free agent in May 2013 after his contract with Siena ran out, and retired from the sport in February 2014.<ref name=\"Career\"/>\n\nBogdani has 74 caps for [[Albania national football team|Albania national team]], making his debut in 1996 and scoring his first goal three years later.<ref name=\"First goal\"/> With 18 goals, he is Albania's all-time top goalscorer, overtaking his former teammate [[Alban Bushi]] in 2011 by netting his 15th goal.<ref name=\"Record\"/> He holds numerous Albanian records, including most goals as substitute and oldest goalscoring in history, and has been dubbed as the best striker to play for the ''Red and Black''.<ref name=\"Records\"/>\n\nFollowing his retirement, Bogdani was initially appointed by [[Albanian Football Association]] as a youth talents scouter, starting the job in September 2014.<ref name=\"Scout\"/> He began his managerial career by being named [[Gianni De Biasi]] assistant in August 2016.<ref name=\"Assistant\"/> In December 2016, he was named manager of Albania under-19 team.<ref name=\"U19\"/>\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Early years===\nBogdani was discovered by local side [[FK Partizani Tirana|Partizani Tirana]] at the age of 10 in a school team competition held in [[Tirana]], where he scored 11 goals in just four games. The young Bogdani then joined Partizani Tirana's academy, where he played through the different age groups and eventually signed his first professional contract with the club in 1994.\n\n===Partizani Tirana===\nBogdani made his professional debut with [[FK Partizani Tirana|Partizani Tirana]] in the [[Albanian Superliga]], playing seven games in the second half of the 1993\u201394 season. The following season, he scored his first goal in a campaign which saw him play 13 games and score 2 goals. The 1997\u201398 campaign would prove to be his most successful in Albanian football as he scored 13 goals in just 15 games before the winter break.\n\n===Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi===\nHis performance at Partizani Tirana attracted the attention of several foreign clubs. Bogdani decided to move to [[Turkey]] at [[Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi]] in the [[S\u00fcper Lig]] playing for the second half of the 1997\u201398 season in 11 games and scoring 1 goal.\n\n===NK Zagreb===\nBogdani later moved to [[Croatia]] with [[Josip Ku\u017ee]]'s (also future coach of Bogdani at the [[Albania national football team|Albania national team]] in 2009) crucial help joining the [[Prva HNL]] club [[NK Zagreb]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Halilaj |first1=Jetmir |title=Nj\u00eb vit pa futboll - Rr\u00ebfimi unik i Bogdanit |url=http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/217158/ |work=[[Panorama Sport]]|language=Albanian |quote=Josip Kuzhe ishte nj\u00eb trajner i zoti, por edhe q\u00eb m\u00eb kishte ndihmuar shum\u00eb. M\u00eb ndihmoi t\u00eb shkoja nga Gen\u00e7lebirligi te Dinamo e Zagrebit, madje pagoi edhe lek\u00eb nga xhepi q\u00eb un\u00eb t\u00eb shkoja atje. \u201cIk, se aty ke t\u00eb ardhme t\u00eb sigurt\u201d. (Jospi Kuze was a great coach,he also helped me a lot moving from Gen\u00e7lebirligi to Dinamo Zagreb, he even paid for me to realise my transfer)}}</ref> In his first season with [[NK Zagreb]], the [[1998\u201399 Prva HNL|1998\u201399]], he played 14 games scoring 9 goals. In the next season [[1999\u20132000 Prva HNL|1999\u20132000]] first-half, he scored 6 goals in 12 games.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Pochini|first1=Danilo|title=Bologna And QPR After Bogdani|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/723/serie-a/2008/08/10/813156/bologna-and-qpr-after-bogdani|website=Goal.com|quote=The 31-year-old has been playing in Serie A since 1999, when he left Dinamo Zagreb for Reggina.}}</ref>\n\n===Reggina===\nWith the first half of the 1999\u20132000 Prva HNL season over, Bogdani was transferred to Italy at the winter break, joining [[Reggina Calcio|Reggina]] on a three-year contract in January 2000.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fUIW1laqYhc|title=Sport Erjon Bogdani tek Regina - (29 Janar 2000)|publisher=YouTube.com|work=TV Klan|language=sq|date=22 November 2019|accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref> He made his Serie A debut on 6 February 2000 against [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]]. Overall in his first season at Reggina he played 10 Serie A games and scored 1 goal. In the [[2000\u201301 Serie A|2000\u201301 season]] he played 19 matches scoring 1 goal and Reggina were relegated in the [[Serie B]]. In the [[2001\u201302 Serie B]] season, Bogdani managed to score 7 goals in 31 games helping Reggina rank in the 3rd place to win promotion in the Serie A. He played overall 11 games and scored 1 goal in the [[2002\u201303 Serie A]]. In the 2003\u201304 season, he was loaned to [[Salernitana Calcio 1919|Salernitana]] in the Serie B.\n\n===Hellas Verona===\nIn the 2004\u201305 season, Bogdani was signed by [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Verona]]. Under coach [[Massimo Ficcadenti]] Bogdani played all 38 matches where he participated as a starter completing 33 full 90-minutes and was the team top-scorer in the Serie B with 17 goals scored. He was ranked 4th in the entire goalscorers classification with 3 goals behind top-scorer [[Gionatha Spinesi]] and 2 goals behind [[Diego Milito]] and [[Francesco Tavano]]. The 2004\u201305 season had the highest number of goals scored in a single season.<ref name=\"Cesena - AlbaniaSoccer\" >[http://albaniasoccer.com/lajme/shqiperi/kombetarja/2578-zyrtare-erjon-bogdani-firmos-me-cezenen.html Zyrtare/ Erjon Bogdani firmos me Cezenen!] AlbaniaSoccer</ref>\n\n===Siena===\nIn the summer of 2005, Bogdani made his return to [[Serie A|Italy's top-flight]], but for [[A.C. Siena]]. He made it his debut on 28 August 2005 against [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] playing a full 90-minute match, which finished in a 2\u20131 victory.<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2005/08/28/italy/serie-a/ac-siena/cagliari-calcio/312152/ Siena vs. Cagliari - 28 August 2005] Soccerway</ref> Bogdani scored his first goal on 21 September 2005 against [[Ascoli Picchio F.C. 1898|Ascoli]], in a match finished in the 1\u20131 draw where his goal was the first of the match, scored in the 45th minute.<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2005/09/21/italy/serie-a/ascoli-calcio/ac-siena/312174/ Ascoli Picchio vs. Siena - 21 September 2005] Soccerway</ref>\n\nOn 28 January 2006 Bogdani scored a [[Hat-trick (football)|hat trick]] of 3 goals against [[U.S. Palermo|Palermo]] where the match finished in the 1\u20133 away victory.<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2006/01/28/italy/serie-a/us-citta-di-palermo/ac-siena/312363/ Palermo vs. Siena - 28 January 2006] Soccerway</ref> In the [[2005\u201306 Serie A|2005\u201306 season]] he registered in total 34 league appearances where he scored in total 11 goals.\n\nHe started another season with Siena as he played in the first match against [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]] on 10 September 2006, where the match finished in a victory 1\u20132.<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2006/09/10/italy/serie-a/ac-chievo-verona/ac-siena/403465/ Chievo vs. Siena - 10 September 2006] Soccerway</ref> He played until the end of the [[2006\u201307 Serie A|2006\u201307 season]]'s first half, where he made 15 appearances and scored 2 goals.\n\n===Chievo Verona===\nOn 11 January 2007 the struggling [[A.C. ChievoVerona]] signed 29-year-old Albanian international striker Bogdani from Serie A rivals AC Siena for an undisclosed fee.<ref>[http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/news/newsid=496148.html Chievo snap up Siena's Bogdani] [[UEFA]].com</ref>\n\nWith Chievo, he made his debut on 14 January 2007 against [[Calcio Catania|Catania]] playing as a starter.<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2007/01/14/italy/serie-a/ac-chievo-verona/calcio-catania/403643/ Chievo vs. Catania - 14 January 2007] Soccerway</ref> He scored twice on 24 February 2007 against [[FC Torino|Torino]], in a match finished in a 3\u20130 victory.<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2007/02/24/italy/serie-a/ac-chievo-verona/torino-fc/403710/ Chievo vs. Torino - 24 February 2007] Soccerway</ref> He established himself as a starter under coach [[Luigi Delneri]] playing in the starting lineup in 16 out 19 matches, scoring in total 5 goals but unable to avoid relegation to Serie B.\n\n====Loan to Livorno====\nBogdani remained in Serie A as he was loaned out to [[A.S. Livorno Calcio|Livorno]] at the start of the 2007\u201308 Serie A season to replace the \"goal machine\" [[Cristiano Lucarelli]].<ref>[http://turismoinalbania.blogspot.al/2007/10/erjon-bogdani-giocatore-del-livorno.html ERJON BOGDANI GIOCATORE DEL LIVORNO] Turismo in Albania</ref> He made his debut with Livorno on 2 September 2007 against [[U.S. Palermo|Palermo]] in a match finished in the 2\u20134 loss, where he came in as a substitute in the 36th minute in place of [[Francesco Tavano]].<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2007/09/02/italy/serie-a/as-livorno-calcio/us-citta-di-palermo/501100/ Livorno vs. Palermo - 2 September 2007] Soccerway</ref> Bogdani scored two goals during the second-half season, first against [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]] on 27 January 2008 in a 1\u20133 loss<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2008/01/27/italy/serie-a/as-livorno-calcio/juventus-fc/501279/ Livorno vs. Juventus - 27 January 2008] Soccerway</ref> and against [[Reggina Calcio|Reggina]] on 19 March 2008 in the match finished in the 1\u20131 draw.<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2008/03/19/italy/serie-a/as-livorno-calcio/reggina-calcio/501371/ Livorno vs. Reggina - 19 March 2008] Soccerway</ref> At the end of the season Livorno relegated to Serie B as they were ranked in the last place of the table. Bogdani registered 28 appearances and only two goals for the entire season.\n\n====Return to Chievo====\nHe returned to Chievo for the [[2008\u201309 Serie A|2008\u201309 season]]. He had a bad season where he wasn't even included in 9 matches and played 12 matches as a starter and 9 as a substitute. He scored only 1 goal for the entire season against [[SS Lazio|Lazio]] on 15 March 2009 in a match finished in the 0\u20133 victory, where Bogdani came in as a substitute following an injury of [[Stephen Makinwa]] in the 20th minute and scored the opening goal in the 27th minute.<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2009/03/15/italy/serie-a/ss-lazio-roma/ac-chievo-verona/666791/ Lazio vs. Chievo - 15 March 2009] Soccerway</ref>\n\nAlmost similar was also the next [[2009\u201310 Serie A|2009\u201310 season]]. He participated in 32 matches playing 12 as a starter and 9 as a substitute where he scored 2 goals and provided 1 assist. On 20 September 2009 against [[Genoa C.F.C.|Genoa]] Bogdani played as a starter and created an immediate impact in the first minutes winning a penalty in the 4th minute converted in goal by [[Michele Marcolini]] and scoring a goal himself 2 minutes later. Chievo won by 3\u20131.<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2009/09/20/italy/serie-a/ac-chievo-verona/genoa-cfc/817307/ Chievo vs. Genoa - 20 September 2009] Soccerway</ref> Due to a dispute with coach [[Domenico Di Carlo]] he was not included in the four penultimate matches of the season.\n\n===Cesena===\nOn 22 July 2010, Bogdani signed with newly promoted Serie A side [[A.C. Cesena|Cesena]] for an undisclosed fee as a free agent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.albaniasoccer.com/lajme/shqiperi/kombetarja/2578-zyrtare-erjon-bogdani-firmos-me-cezenen.html|title=Zyrtare/ Erjon Bogdani firmos me Cezenen!|trans-title=Official/ Erjon Bogdani signs for Cesena|publisher=AlbaniaSoccer|language=Albanian|date=22 July 2010|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref> He signed a contract until the end of the [[2010\u201311 Serie A|2010\u201311 season]], with an option of a further season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arkivalajmeve.com/Bogdani-firmos-per-nje-sezon-me-skuadren-e-ezenes.1046901982/|title=Bogdani firmos p\u00ebr nj\u00eb sezon me skuadr\u00ebn e \u00c7ezen\u00ebs|trans-title=Bogdani signs for a season with the team of Cesena|publisher=Arkiva Shqiptare e Lajmeve|language=Albanian|date=24 July 2010|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref> Bogdani took squad number 70, and made his debut by starting in the goalless draw versus [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] in the opening matchday on 28 August.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2010/08/28/italy/serie-a/as-roma/ac-cesena/989956/|title=Roma vs. Cesena 0 \u2013 0|publisher=Soccerway|date=28 August 2010|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref> His first score-sheet contributions came in his second appearance two weeks later in the 2\u20130 home win over [[A.C. Milan|Milan]], netting the opener and also setting up [[Emanuele Giaccherini]] for the second.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://football-italia.net/sa1011/ces-mil.html|title=Cesena 2\u20130 Milan|publisher=Football Italia|date=11 September 2010|accessdate=14 September 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100914062126/http://www.football-italia.net/sa1011/ces-mil.html|archivedate=14 September 2010|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He was named \"Man of the match\" for his performance, and he followed that up by netting the winner versus [[U.S. Lecce|Lecce]] the next week.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/association=ita/news/newsid=1533765.html|title=Inter and Cesena set Serie A pace|publisher=UEFA.com|date=19 September 2010|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref> He finished his first season at ''Cavallucci Marini'' by scoring 8 goals in 35 league appearances, being the second scorer of the team, only one goal less than [[Luis Antonio Jim\u00e9nez|Luis Jim\u00e9nez]]. It was his highest tally since the 2005\u201306 season.\n\nBogdani lost his place in the [[2011\u201312 Serie A|next season]], being reduced to playing only at [[2011\u201312 Coppa Italia|cup]] games.<ref name=\"Gubbio\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ilrestodelcarlino.it/cesena/sport/calcio/2011/11/30/629408-coppa_italia_cesena.shtml|title=Coppa Italia, il Cesena doma il Gubbio 3-0|trans-title=Italian Cup, Cesena dominates Gubbio 3-0|publisher=Il Resto del Carlino|language=Italian|date=30 November 2011|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref> He scored his first goal of the season on 21 August in the third round match of Coppa Italia's Section 8, the winner versus [[Ascoli Calcio 1898|Ascoli]] in the 119th minute, having came on as substitute in 106th minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2011/08/21/italy/coppa-italia/ac-cesena/ascoli-calcio/1191151/|title=Cesena vs. Ascoli 1 \u2013 0|publisher=Soccerway|date=21 August 2011|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref> Bogdani's second goal came in the next cup match versus [[A.S. Gubbio 1910|Gubbio]], netting the opener with a penalty kick in a 3\u20130 home win, which allowed Cesena to progress to round of 16.<ref name=\"Gubbio\"/> After being used very scarcely in league during the first part of the season,<ref name=\"Cesena\">{{cite web|url=http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/bogdani-drejt-sienes-cezena-nis-presionin/|title=Bogdani drejt Sien\u00ebs, \u00c7ezena nis \"presionin\"|trans-title=Bogdani towards Siena, Cesena starts the \u201cpressure\u201d|publisher=Panorama Sport|language=Albanian|date=28 January 2012|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref> he left the club in January 2012 during the winter transfer window.<ref name=\"Cesena\"/>\n\n===Return to Siena===\nBogdani returned to [[AC Siena]] by signing a two-year contract on the final day of the winter transfer window.<ref>[http://albaniasoccer.com/lajme/shqiperi/kombetarja/5902-zyrtare-bogdani-le-cezenen-per-sienen.html Zyrtare/ Bogdani le Cezenen per Sienen] AlbaniaSoccer</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/31012012/58/serie-inter-sell-motta-psg-window-closes.html|title=Serie A \u2013 Inter sell Motta to PSG as window closes|date=31 January 2012|accessdate=1 February 2012|publisher=Eurosport|author=}}</ref> He made his debut with the Tuscans 22 February 2012, in the home defeat against [[Calcio Catania|Catania]]. He scored his first goal in the league 26 February 2012 in the 4\u20131 win against [[U.S. Citt\u00e0 di Palermo|Palermo]]. He scored again in the next two weeks against [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] and [[A.C. Cesena|Cesena]], his former team. Bogdani concluded the season with 11 appearances and 4 goals.<ref name=\"Soccerway matches\" >[https://int.soccerway.com/players/erjon-bogdani/4334/matches/ Erjon Bogdani matches] Soccerway</ref>\n\nThe following season he began by playing from the first minute in Siena-[[Vicenza Calcio|Vicenza]] (4\u20132), valid for the third round of the [[Coppa Italia|Italian Cup]], going out to 33 of recovery instead of [[Michele Paolucci]]. He made his debut in the league on 26 August against [[Torino F.C.|Torino]] (0\u20130), scored his first goal of the season on 31 October in Cagliari-Siena (4\u20132). Bogdani scored his second goal against [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]] on 20 January 2013. He came in as a substitute to score in the 63rd minute the only goal of the match which gave Siena the 1\u20130 victory.<ref>[http://www.sportishqiptar.com.al/newsite/2013/01/21/bogdani-gol-fitoreje-dhe-sherr-me-portierin-romero/ Bogdani, gol fitoreje dhe sherr me portierin Romero] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170810051216/http://www.sportishqiptar.com.al/newsite/2013/01/21/bogdani-gol-fitoreje-dhe-sherr-me-portierin-romero/ |date=10 August 2017 }} [[Sporti Shqiptar]]</ref>\n\nAfter his contract with Siena expired at the end of the season, Bogdani didn't move to any club in the 2013 summer transfer window.<ref>[http://albaniasoccer.com/lajme/shqiperi/kombetarja/7796-levizjet-mbyllet-afati-kalimtar-er-bomber-pa-kontrate.html Levizjet/ Mbyllet afati kalimtar, Er-Bomber pa kontrat\u00eb] AlbaniaSoccer</ref> On 11 February 2014 Bogdani confirmed to have [[Retirement|retired]] from football.<ref name=\"lamtumira\" >[http://www.zathur.net/bogu-jep-lamtumiren-futbollit/ Bogu i jep lamtumir\u00ebn futbollit] Zathur.net</ref>\n\n==International career==\n===Youth===\n;Under-21\nBogdani first became part of the [[Albania national under-21 football team|Albania U21 team]] in 1996, where he scored on his official debut in a [[1998 UEFA European Under-21 Football Championship qualification]] match against [[Portugal national under-21 football team|Portugal]] on 9 October 1996. Following his goal however, he was sent off after receiving the first red card of his career just 4 minutes after scoring his first international goal and Albania went on to lose the game 4\u20132.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.11v11.com/matches/albania-v-portugal-09-october-1996-266735/|title=Albania v Portugal, 09 October 1996|publisher=11v11|date=9 October 1996|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref> Overall he made 7 official appearances and scored 1 goal as Albania finished Group 9 in 5th place.<ref name=\"UEFA profile\">{{UEFA player|29077}}</ref>\n\n;Under-23\nBogdani was called up to [[Albania national under-23 football team|Albania under-23]] by coach [[Sulejman Mema]] to participate in the [[Football at the 1997 Mediterranean Games|1997 Mediterranean Games football tournament]], which began on 8 June in [[Southern Italy]]. Albania U23 were shorted in Group B among [[Yugoslavia Olympic football team|Yugoslavia]] and [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italy]]. Bogdani played as a half-time substitute for [[Mahir Halili]] against Yugoslavia U23 and scored in the 60th minute the only Albania U23's goal in a 4\u20131 loss. In the second fixture against Italy U23 he was an unused substitute.<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesm/medgames97.html Mediterranean Games 1997 (Italy)] RSSSF</ref>\n\n===Senior===\n====1996\u201303: Beginnings====\nBogdani was first introduced to the [[Albania national football team|Albania senior squad]] by manager [[Neptun Bajko]] in April 1996 for the friendly match versus [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]]. He came at the last minutes as a substitute with the match ending in a goalless draw.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eu-football.info/_match.php?id=10629|title=Football MATCH: 24.04.1996 Bosnia & Herzegovina v Albania|publisher=EU-Football.info|date=24 April 1996|accessdate=29 March 2018}}</ref> Later that year, in December, Bogdani was called up again for the [[1998 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)#Group 9|1998 FIFA World Cup qualification]] match against [[Northern Ireland national football team|Northern Ireland]] in which Bogdani was an unused substitute. Albania lost 2\u20130 at [[Windsor Park]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/1996/12/14/europe/wc-qualifying-europe/northern-ireland/albania/630279/|title=Northern Ireland vs. Albania 2 \u2013 0|publisher=Soccerway|date=14 December 1996|accessdate=29 March 2018}}</ref> His second appearance came two years later in another friendly versus [[Cyprus national football team|Cyprus]] on 19 August 1998 where he again came as a substitute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eu-football.info/_match.php?id=11003|title=Football MATCH: 19.08.1998 Cyprus v Albania|publisher=EU-Football.info|date=19 August 1998|accessdate=29 March 2018}}</ref>\n\nBogdani scored his first international goal on 10 February 1999 in the 2\u20130 friendly win over [[Macedonia national football team|Macedonia]].<ref name=\"First goal\">{{cite web|url=https://eu-football.info/_match.php?id=11419|title=Football MATCH: 10.02.1999 Albania v Macedonia|publisher=EU-Football.info|date=10 February 1999|accessdate=29 March 2018}}</ref> He continued to be part of the team under [[Astrit Hafizi]] management in the [[UEFA Euro 2000 qualifying]], where Albania was placed in [[UEFA Euro 2000 qualifying Group 2|Group 2]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2000/teams/team=2/matches/index.html|title=Albania UEFA Euro 2000|publisher=UEFA.com|accessdate=29 March 2018}}</ref> He made 6 appearances during the qualifying phase, including one as starter, as Albania finished the group in 5th place with 7 points.<ref name=\"EURO 2000\">{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2000/standings/round=1165/group=907/index.html|title=Preliminary round Group 2|publisher=UEFA.com|accessdate=29 March 2018}}</ref>\n\nBogdani didn't found more space in the next qualifying campaign, the [[2002 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 UEFA Group 9|2002 FIFA World Cup qualification]], in which he managed to play only four matches. He was not seen as starter by manager [[Medin Zhega]] before players such as [[Igli Tare]], [[Alban Bushi]] and [[Altin Rraklli]].<ref name=\"Soccerway matches\"/> He scored his next international goals in form of a brace in the 3\u20130 home win over [[Malta national football team|Malta]] on 15 November 2000.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eu-football.info/_match.php?id=24550|title=Football MATCH: 15.11.2000 Albania v Malta|publisher=EU-Football.info|date=15 November 2000|accessdate=29 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n====2004\u201305: Injury and return as protagonist====\nBogdani missed out almost the entire [[UEFA Euro 2004 qualifying Group 10|UEFA Euro 2004 qualifying]] due to injury suffered at club level, participating only one time on 7 June 2003 against [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]] where he was an unused substitute under coach [[Hans-Peter Briegel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2003/06/07/europe/european-championship-qualification/ireland-republic/albania/49366/|title=Republic of Ireland vs. Albania 2 \u2013 1|publisher=Soccerway|date=7 June 2003|accessdate=29 March 2018}}</ref>\n\nHaving been out of the team for more than 18 months, Bogdani returned in February 2005 for the matchday 5 of [[2006 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 UEFA Group 2|2006 FIFA World Cup qualification]] campaign against [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]] in which he appeared as a second-half substitute for fellow striker Tare.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eu-football.info/_match.php?id=249|title=Football MATCH: 09.02.2005 Albania v Ukraine|publisher=EU-Football.info|date=9 February 2005|accessdate=29 March 2018}}</ref> Then he was put as starter in the next matches after a good run on club level, notably scoring in the loss to [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]] and win versus [[Kazakhstan national football team|Kazakhstan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eu-football.info/_match.php?id=262|title=Football MATCH: 08.06.2005 Denmark v Albania|publisher=EU-Football.info|date=8 June 2005|accessdate=29 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://eu-football.info/_match.php?id=264|title=Football MATCH: 03.09.2005 Albania v Kazakhstan|publisher=EU-Football.info|date=8 June 2005|accessdate=29 March 2018}}</ref> Then he scored a brace in the 2\u20132 draw versus Ukraine in the penultimate qualifying match which gave him four for the campaign, making him top goalscorer of the team, as Albania finished Group 2 at 5th place, leaving behind Georgia and Kazakhstan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tables/2006q.html#eur|title=World Cup 2006 Qualifying|publisher=RSSF.com|accessdate=29 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n====2006\u201309: Half-century caps and double-figures goals====\n\nBogdani continued to lead Albania's attacking force in the [[UEFA Euro 2008 qualifying]], playing 11 matches, all of them as starter, and was along with [[Altin Haxhi]] the most used player.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2008/teams/team=2/squad/index.html|title=Albania UEFA Euro 2008 squad|publisher=UEFA.com|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref> He scored only once during the qualifiers, the temporary equalizer in an eventual 4\u20132 home defeat to [[Belarus national football team|Belarus]] on 17 November 2007 in the penultimate matchday of [[UEFA Euro 2008 qualifying Group G|Group G]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2008/matches/round=2241/match=83699/postmatch/report/index.html|title=Belarus brush Albania aside|publisher=UEFA.com|date=17 November 2007|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref> Albania failed once again to qualify at a major tournament as they finished Group G in 5th position with 11 points from 12 matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2008/standings/round=2241/group=2636/index.html|title=Qualifying round Group G|publisher=UEFA.com|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref>\n\nBogdani played his first [[2010 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)#Group 1|2010 FIFA World Cup qualification]] match by scoring the opener against [[Malta national football team|Malta]], his 9th international goal, in an eventual 3\u20130 win at [[Qemal Stafa Stadium]] in the second match of [[2010 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 UEFA Group 1|Group 1]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/1646/wcq-2010-europe/2008/09/10/858461/albania-crush-malta-in-tirana|title=Albania Crush Malta In Tirana|publisher=Goal.com|date=10 September 2008|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref> Later on 6 June 2009, Bogdani scored his 10th international goal against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]], becoming only the fifth player to achieve the feat. His goal however was only the temporary equalizer the minute after Portugal's opener, as Albania lost 1\u20132 at injury time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/soccer-world-portugal/soccer-late-bruno-alves-goal-revives-portugal-qualifying-hopes-idUKL656768020090606|title=Soccer-Late Bruno Alves goal revives Portugal qualifying hopes|publisher=Reuters|date=6 June 2009|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref> Bogdani made his 50th international appearance in the friendly versus [[Cyprus national football team|Cyprus]] in August 2009, netting the third goal in a 6\u20131 home win which was Albania's largest ever victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2009/08/12/world/friendlies/albania/cyprus/826319/|title=Albania vs. Cyprus 6 \u2013 1|publisher=Soccerway|date=12 August 2009|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref> With this goal he overtook Igli Tare and Sokol Kushta to become Albania's 4th goalscorer of all time. Bogdani scored his next goal in the next qualifying match against Denmark to give Albania a 1\u20131 draw.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/1863/world-cup-2010/2009/09/10/1491349/albania-1-1-denmark-danes-retain-top-spot-despite|title=Albania 1-1 Denmark: Danes Retain Top Spot Despite Disappointing Draw|publisher=Goal.com|date=9 September 2009|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref> It was the first time that Bogdani had scored in three consecutive matches. Albania finished Group 1 in 5th place with only 7 points and 6 goals scored, with Bogdani netting half of them.\n\n====2010\u201311: Albania top scorer, UEFA Euro 2012 qualifying====\nBogdani began his [[UEFA Euro 2012 qualifying]] by playing as a starter in the opening [[UEFA Euro 2012 qualifying Group D|Group D]] match versus [[Romania national football team|Romania]] as Albania drew 1\u20131 at [[Stadionul Ceahl\u0103ul]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2012/matches/round=15171/match=2002088/postmatch/report/index.html|title=Albania end losing streak against Romania|publisher=UEFA.com|date=3 September 2010|accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref> It was also Albania's first draw versus ''Tricolorii'' since 1949 after 9 consecutive defeats.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.11v11.com/teams/albania/tab/opposingTeams/opposition/Romania/|title=Albania national football team: record v Romania|publisher=11v11.com|accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref> On 9 February 2011, Bogdani played in the 1\u20132 friendly loss to [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]], entering in Albania's top 10 appearance maker list.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sport.albeu.com/kryetitull/sllovenia-mposht-shqiperine/29764/|title=Sllovenia mposht Shqip\u00ebrin\u00eb (VIDEO)|trans-title=Slovania defeats Albania (VIDEO)|publisher=Sport.albeu.com|date=9 February 2010|accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref> Later on 26 March 2011, Bogdani assisted [[Hamdi Salihi]]'s winner against Belarus with a header to give Albania the 1\u20130 win at Qemal Stafa Stadium, the first ever against them.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2012/matches/round=15171/match=2002103/postmatch/report/index.html|title=Salihi strike secures victory for Albania|publisher=UEFA.com|date=26 March 2011|accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.11v11.com/teams/albania/tab/opposingTeams/opposition/Belarus/|title=Albania national football team: record v Belarus|publisher=11v11.com|accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref> It was also Bogdani's 60 international appearance, overtaking [[Rudi Vata]] in the process.\n\nBogdani scored his first goal in the qualifiers on 2 September 2011 against the [[FIFA World Cup]]-winners [[France national football team|France]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2012/matches/round=15171/match=2002100/postmatch/report/index.html|title=France squeeze past Albania to stay top|publisher=UEFA.com|date=2 September 2011|accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref> With this goal Bogdani leveled [[Alban Bushi]] to become joint all-time top goalscorer of Albania with 14 goals. He broke the record four days later in the next qualifying match,<ref name=\"Record\">{{cite web|url=http://albaniasoccer.com/lajme/shqiperi/kombetarja/5274-ne-fokus-bogdani-thyen-rekordin-e-bushit-rekord-15-golesh.html|title=Ne fokus/ Bogdani thyen rekordin e Bushit, rekord 15-golesh|trans-title=In focus/ Bogdani breaks Bushi's record, a 15 goals record|publisher=AlbaniaSoccer|language=Albanian|date=6 September 2011|accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref> a 2\u20131 away loss versus [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2012/matches/round=15171/match=2002109/postmatch/report/index.html|title=Luxembourg beat Albania for first win|publisher=UEFA.com|author=David Babaev|date=6 September 2011|accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref> In the post-match interview, Bogdani stated that he was consider to retire from national team but reverted his consideration following a conversation with the [[Albanian Football Association]] president [[Armand Duka]] declaring that he will stay for another qualification campaign if Albania national team needs him and of course if he would be in a good running form.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://albaniasoccer.com/lajme/shqiperi/kombetarja/5435-kombetarja-bogdaninese-nevojitem-qendroj-per-edicionin-e-ardhshem.htm|title=Kombetarja/ Bogdani:Nese nevojitem, qendroj per edicionin e ardhshem|trans-title=National team/ Bogdani: If I'm needed, I stay for the next edition|publisher=AlbaniaSoccer|language=Albanian|date=9 October 2011|accessdate=3 April 2018}}{{Dead link|date=December 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> He also described 2011 as one of the best years of his career.<ref name=\"Er-Bomber\">{{cite web|url=http://www.arkivalajmeve.com/Superviti-i-Erjon-Bogdanit-rekordmen-dhe-baba.1047161979/|title=Superviti i Erjon Bogdanit, rekordmen dhe baba|trans-title=Superyear of Erjon Bogdani, record man and father|publisher=Arkiva Shqiptare e Lajmeve|language=Albanian|date=9 October 2011|accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n====2012\u201313: Final years under De Biasi====\nNow a veteran, Bogdani continued to be a part of the national team even after the appointment of manager [[Gianni De Biasi]], who was known for having a liking for youth players. He scored his first goal under De Biasi on 22 May 2012, his 16th with a penalty, in a 2\u20131 friendly win over [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]] at [[Campo de F\u00fatbol de Vallecas]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arkivalajmeve.com/Shqiperia-fiton-miqesoren-me-Katarin-shenojne-Bakaj-e-Bogdani.1047240409/|title=Shqip\u00ebria fiton miq\u00ebsoren me Katarin, sh\u00ebnojn\u00eb Bakaj e Bogdani|trans-title=Albania wins the friendly with Qatar, Bakaj and Bogdani scored|publisher=Arkiva Shqiptare e Lajmeve|work=BalkanWeb.com|language=Albanian|date=22 May 2012|accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nFor the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2014 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]], De Biasi had introduced young forwards into the team to create more competition for the starting eleven. Young forwards such as [[Edgar \u00c7ani]], [[Armando Sadiku]] and [[Bekim Balaj]] provided competition for the established and mature internationals which were Bogdani and [[Hamdi Salihi]]. He played as a substitute in the opening [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 UEFA Group E|Group E]] match versus Cyprus, entering at 72nd minute in place of [[Emiljano Vila]], only to fire a 30-yard strike into the net in the 87th minute to secure a 3\u20131 win, a goal which many considered to be the best international goal of his career.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/news/newsid=1856695.html#/|title=Albania leave it late against Cyprus|publisher=UEFA.com|date=7 September 2013|accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref> It was his 69th match for Albania, which made him the fifth player with most appearances, overtaking Igli Tare and Alban Bushi. He started in the second match against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] but was replaced in the 55th minute as Albania lost 0\u20132.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/worldcup/season=2014/matches/round=2000294/match=2008659/postmatch/report/index.html|title=Switzerland come good against Albania|publisher=UEFA.com|date=11 September 2013|accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nBogdani begun 2013 by netting his 18th international goal, a first-half header, in the friendly loss against [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]] on 6 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oranews.tv/article/shqiperia-e-nis-me-humbje-mposhtet-21-nga-gjeorgjia|title=Shqip\u00ebria e nis me humbje, mposhtet 2:1 nga Gjeorgjia|trans-title=Albania starts with loss, defeated 2:1 by Georgia|publisher=Ora News|language=Albanian|date=6 February 2013|accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref> He played as a late substitute in the qualifying match versus [[Norway national football team|Norway]] as Albania took their first ever win versus them thanks to Hamdi Salihi's winner.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/worldcup/season=2014/matches/round=2000294/match=2008649/postmatch/report/index.html|title=Albania beat the freeze in Norway|publisher=UEFA.com|language=Albanian|date=22 March 2013|accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref> This proved to be his last competitive match. Bogdani [[Captain (association football)|captained]] Albania for the first time in his career four days later in the friendly match against [[Lithuania national football team|Lithuania]] in his 74th international appearance, playing for 70 minutes before making place for [[Lorik Cana]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.panorama.com.al/luhet-shqiperi-lituani-debuton-valdet-rama/|title=Shqip\u00ebria fiton miq\u00ebsoren me Lituanin\u00eb, 4-1|trans-title=Albania wins the friendly with Lithuania 4-1|publisher=Panorama.com.al|language=Albanian|date=26 March 2013|accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n====Retirement====\nOn 11 February 2014, Bogdani confirmed to have [[Retirement|retired]] from the played football, thus ending his 17-year international career.<ref name=\"lamtumira\"/> At the time, he was Albania's fourth player with most appearances. He is currently the top goalscorer with 18 goals.<ref name=\"Records\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/bogdani-intlg.html|title=Erion Bogdani - Goals in International Matches|publisher=RSSSF.com|author=Roberto Mamrud|accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref> He also hold records for most goals scored for Albania at [[FIFA World Cup qualification]] (8),<ref name=\"Records\"/> and most goals scored as a substitute (4). In addition, Bogdani is also the oldest player at 35 years, 10 month, 23 days to score a goal for Albania.<ref name=\"Records\"/>\n\n==Managerial career==\n===Albania national team===\nPrincipally Bogdani started working as youth talents Scouter at [[Albania national football team]], where he was named on 12 August 2014 by [[FSHF]].<ref name=\"Scout\">{{cite web|url=http://fshf.org/en/bogdani-scout-of-red-and-black-teams/|title=Bogdani, scout of red and black teams|publisher=FSHF.org|date=16 September 2014|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 August 2015, he was named as the Albania national team assistant manager by the national head coach [[Gianni De Biasi]] for replacing the departed [[Altin Lala]].<ref name=\"Assistant\">{{cite web|url=http://klankosova.tv/bogdani-emerohet-ndihmes-i-de-biasit/|title=Bogdani em\u00ebrohet ndihm\u00ebs i De Biasit|trans-title=Bogdani named De Biasi's assistant|publisher=Klan Kosova|language=Albanian|date=29 August 2015|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Albania under-19===\nFollowing naming of [[Paolo Tramezzani]] fellow assistant manager of De Biasi at Albania national team as a National teams director, on 9 December 2016 Bogdani was named as the [[Albania national under-19 football team]] manager.<ref name=\"U19\">{{cite web|url=http://fshf.org/?tv=prezantohen-trajneret-e-ekipeve-kombetare-u-21-dhe-u-19|title=Prezantohen trajner\u00ebt e ekipeve komb\u00ebtare U-21 dhe U-19|trans-title=Managers of national team U19 and U21 are presented|publisher=FSHF.org|language=Albanian|date=9 December 2016|accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2017 he had his first gathering with Albania U19 where he participated in the Roma Caput Mundi Tournament developed from 27 February\u20133 March 2017. He won its first ever tournament which he participated, beating [[Romania national under-19 football team|Romania U19]] 2\u20130 in the Final.<ref>[http://www.fshf.org/index.php/sq/lajme/5444-u-19-fiton-turneun-roma-caput-mundi U-19 fiton turneun \"Roma Caput Mundi\"] [[FSHF]].org</ref> Prior the Final he did won the opening match against [[Malta national under-19 football team|Malta U19]] 2\u20131, winning then by 2\u20130 against [[England national under-19 football team|England national under-19 team]] of high-schools and beating [[Italy national under-19 football team|Italy national under-19 team]] of Diletanti 4\u20132 by [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|Penalty shoot-out]]. During this tournament, did caught attention a young talent [[Sadik Cela]] of [[PAOK FC|PAOK]] under-20 who scored 3 goals.<ref>[http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/erjon-bogdani-e-fillon-me-fitore-karrieren-si-trajner-te-u-19/ Erjon Bogdani e fillon me fitore karrier\u00ebn si trajner te U-19] [[Panorama Sport]]</ref><ref>[http://www.fshf.org/index.php/sq/lajme/5437-kombetarja-u-19-fiton-perballe-anglise-2-0 Kombetarja U-19 fiton perballe Anglise 2-0] [[FSHF]].org</ref><ref>[http://www.fshf.org/index.php/sq/lajme/5443-u-19-fiton-me-penallti-ndaj-italise-neser-luhet-finallja-perballe-rumanise U-19 fiton me penallti ndaj Italise, neser luhet finallja perballe Rumanise] [[FSHF]].org</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===Club===\n{{updated|19 May 2013}} <ref>{{Soccerway|erjon-bogdani/4334|accessdate=22 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.footballdatabase.eu/football.joueurs.erjon.bogdani.2438.en.html|title=Football : Erjon Bogdani|publisher=Football Database|date=7 July 2016|accessdate=7 July 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"NFT profile\" >{{NFT player|id=34|name=Bogdani, Erjon|accessdate=7 July 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"UEFA profile\" />\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Club statistics\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|[[FK Partizani Tirana|Partizani Tirana]]\n|[[1993\u201394 Albanian Superliga|1993\u201394]]\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[Albanian Superliga]]\n|7||0||0||0||0||0||7||0\n|-\n|[[1994\u201395 Albanian Superliga|1994\u201395]]\n|13||2||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||13||2\n|-\n|[[1995\u201396 Albanian Superliga|1995\u201396]]\n|20||2||0||0||2<ref group=\"lower-alpha\">All appearance(s) in [[1995\u201396 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]]</ref>||0||22||2\n|-\n|[[1996\u201397 Albanian Superliga|1996\u201397]]\n|14||4||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||15||4\n|-\n|[[1997\u201398 Albanian Superliga|1997\u201398]]\n|15||13||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\